## 1. Small code improvements first

### Add null/session checks in `completeSalesPointSelection`

Right now this can fail with NPE if session expired:

```java
UserSession session = redisSessionService.findBySessionId(sessionId);
```

Use:

```java
if (sessionId == null || sessionId.isBlank()) {
    throw new TechnicalException("Session id must not be blank");
}

UserSession session = redisSessionService.findBySessionId(sessionId);

if (session == null) {
    throw new TechnicalException("Session expired");
}

if (session.getSalesPoints() == null || session.getSalesPoints().isEmpty()) {
    throw new TechnicalException("No sales points available for user");
}
```

### Avoid hardcoded handoff TTL

Replace:

```java
handoff.setExpiresAt(Instant.now().plusSeconds(60));
```

with property later:

```java
handoff.setExpiresAt(Instant.now().plusSeconds(arthurSecurityProperties.getHandoff().getTtlSeconds()));
```

For now, okay to keep `60`.

### Remove Keycloak-specific method later

This is Keycloak-specific:

```java
private String toInternalUrl(String url) {
    return url.replace("keycloak.kubernetes.localhost", "keycloak.ns-keycloak.svc.cluster.local");
}
```

Since you’re moving to Ping, this should eventually be removed or made generic/configurable.

